          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "AddContactAddress",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " stored procedure is designed to manage contact information within a database. It either updates an existing contact's address details if the email already exists in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Contact.ContactAddress",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table or inserts a new contact record if the email is not found. The procedure ensures that changes are made within a transaction to maintain data integrity and uses error handling to manage exceptions."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
